  <item type="comment">The myth of Damari and Guyala - see 1.5.  Guyala was a sensible man, who tried to organize the details of life logically and easily; but his brother Damari was silly and obstructive, often being intent on making things as complex and difficult as he could.  Told by Dick Moses in the coastal dialect (recorded at Yarrabah on 15 December 1970; duration 12 1/4 minutes).</item>
