      <item type="number">98</item>
      <item type="gls">[I'll tell this to Guyala when] by-and-by [he] asks me [where I was in the battle, Damari thought to himself.]</item>
      <item type="comment">Damari uses verbal derivational affix -:din in the 'inanimate agent' sense, so that the verb baga"di-n in 97 is still transitive (this is clearly shown by the O pronominal form nanan); he is thus implying that his wounds were caused accidentally.  In fact they were self-inflicted, and he should have used the 'reflexive' sense of -:di-n, deriving an intransitive stem, and said nayu gula baga:di-n.  See 4.2.5.</item>
